personality:
Ako is initially introduced as a reserved and somewhat abrasive girl, quick to lash out and treat those around her rudely and inconsiderately. Eventually, it is revealed that this behavior is due in part to Minor Land's takeover of Major Land and her belief that she would be forced to save everyone on her own.

In her Masked form, Cure Muse is very aloof and mysterious. She insists that she's not an ally of the other Cures, though she does often show up to lend them her aid. She does not speak in this form, instead allowing
Dodory
 to speak for her.

After her identity as Cure Muse is revealed and she finally joins the rest of the Pretty Cures outright, Ako lets down her cold exterior somewhat. She reveals herself to be a sweet and considerate girl who enjoys music and loves to sing. She acts somewhat mature for her age and seems capable of understanding things most kids her age wouldn't.

Despite being the Princess of Major Land, Ako has little sense of grandeur about herself. She often insists that people simply call her by her name rather than her title.

name: Shirayuki Hime
personality:
Hime is a spoiled fashionista who became a
Cure
 to save the
Blue Sky Kingdom
. Despite her brave decision, she is easily scared and tries to escape from danger in the middle of fights. Because of her shyness, she never had friends until meeting
Aino Megumi
. Hime is also stubborn and headstrong, and can be impatient and determined, as shown in
episode 23
, when she tries to persuade Iona to instantly accept their offer to join their team. She can also be forceful and at times selfish, once hurrying the girls back to the embassy due to being hungry.

Hime is often shown to have a wild imagination of sorts. In one instance, she imagines that Cure Lovely is splitting up the Happiness Charge Pretty Cure team in favor of a new partnership with Cure Fortune.
She also imagines Yuko, who was taking care of Phantom, hugging Phantom romantically when she eavesdrops on the two.

name: Sora Harewataru
personality:
Sora is a highly athletic individual who always gives her best, no matter the obstacles she faces. She has dedicated herself to rigorous training every day in pursuit of becoming a hero, inspired by
a person
 who once saved her when she was a child. Despite her commitment to heroism, Sora also displays a polite and kind demeanor, particularly towards children. However, her strong sense of justice and good-hearted nature can sometimes lead to recklessness, causing her to overlook the bigger picture. Sora is also very honest and tends to share too much personal information. While she can be a bit overly protective, she is capable of recognizing when she has made assumptions that go too far.

Due to struggles with social skills since childhood, Sora is somewhat socially awkward. But with the support of her friends, she is learning to adapt to new environments.

name: Suzumura Sango
personality: Sango is a stylish 1st-year middle school student who loves cute things. She's very kind and can get along with anyone. Her family owns a beauty parlor, so she knows a lot about makeup and cosmetics. Despite her kindness, she lacks self-confidence and usually just goes with the flow, but gradually learns to believe in herself.

name: Takizawa Asuka
personality:
Asuka is an athletic 3rd year middle school student with a strong sense of justice. At first glance, she appears to be cool and unapproachable, especially towards Yuriko. However, she is actually a very reliable big sister type. In fact, she really loves to cook and play cute animal games.

Despite normally being a sisterly figure to her younger friends, Asuka can be extremely reckless and sometimes has a short temper, which make conflicts arise that she usually doesn't intend to cause.

name: Tategami Aoi
personality: Aoi is an enthusiastic and bold individual, who is brave and passionate. Her strength seems boundless, and she is always eager to try new things. Above everything else, she desires freedom and feels stifled by the strict rules at home, which require her to behave and dress more appropriately. Initially, Aoi's competitive nature makes it hard for her to accept her own shortcomings, but she eventually learns to let go and embrace her personality, which is "hard and chewy," and develops her own unique musical style.

name: Tengen Kouga
personality:
Kouga is strict, but cares deeply about his friends. However, he is very harsh since he expects high results from others. He usually has no time for discussions that are off-topic. His relationship with his family is very personal and he doesn't allow those to express it publicly. He gets easily aggressive especially when his relationship with Maito is brought up. Kouga heavily dislikes causalities and disruptions, especially when he takes being a Pretty Cure seriously. However, he learns to accept Gaku, Hayato, and Maito as his friends.

As Cure Kagura, he tends to be quite poetic.

name: Tsukikage Yuri
personality:
Yuri is calm and composed, well known for her cool attitude and her frequently chart-topping exam scores at school. She cares for little and is initially cold towards Tsubomi and Erika. After losing Cologne, she became quiet and withdrawn, fearful of causing others to feel burdened by her or risk losing someone else she cherishes. She believed it would be impossible for her to become a Pretty Cure again and was deeply saddened. Before this happened, she was shown to be overly confident and bold. She wouldn't listen to Cologne when she believed she didn't need a partner for help until Cologne died for her.

Her true personality is one of contentment and maturity. She can be stubborn when she sets her mind to something but begins to open up as she spends more time with the group. She shows a more friendly side to herself by this point. Although generally mature, she can sometimes be oblivious to other's romantic feelings for her.

name: Tsukimiya Sasana
personality:
Sasana is mischievous and sensual. He is broad-minded and shows responsibility as head of the dance club. He is willing to give advice, passionate, encouraging, sassy, charismatic, and is admired by students for this.

Whenever students fail, he reassures them no matter what. Sasana is very accepting, due to his beliefs that everyone has their own freedom. However, his advice can also unintentionally hurt those, like Hayato.

name: Usami Ichika
personality: Ichika is cheerful and upbeat, and she loves all kinds of sweets. She's very creative and excels at decorating and making animal-shaped sweets, as she's always coming up with new ideas. However, her cooking skills and schooling could use some improvement. Ichika has a way of making others smile through her pure and genuine feelings and the heart she puts into everything she does. She's usually very perky, and when she's really excited, she hops around much like a rabbit. Ichika can be clumsy at times and is fairly emotional.

name: Wakamiya Henri
personality: Henri is generally friendly towards others. He is shown to have a preference for feminine clothing. Despite being mocked by others for this choice, Henri is adamant and is not swayed by their words of mockery. However, Henri is shown to be insecure with the passing of time as it continues to advance quickly, until he learns to accept it thanks to his friends supporting him. He can be stubborn, as when he tried to convince Homare to come to Russia with him.

name: Yakushiji Saaya
personality: Saaya is a kind girl who is gentle and soft-spoken. She acts like an angel towards everyone. Despite having been a famous child actor, she was once lost and uncertain of her own future until she realizes her hidden dream of becoming a doctor. She also has some peculiar interests, like a love for spicy foods and enthusiasm towards sets of tools. She also has a hidden competitive streak.

name: Yamabuki Inori
personality:
Inori is calm, gentle, quiet, and shy, making her stand out somewhat from the other three relatively rambunctious
Fresh!
 Cures. She tends to worry about what others think of her, and gets embarrassed easily. She is very protective of those she cares for, though she usually prefers to avoid disputes whenever possible. While she normally goes with the flow, she can also be quick-witted and nimble when the situation calls for it. She adores animals, and aspires to become a veterinarian like her parents when she is older.

When she is first introduced, Inori is a reserved girl with low self-confidence; she seeks to improve on this aspect of herself, however, and over the course of the series is shown to grow more confident.

name: Yotsuba Alice
personality:
Alice is the mistress and heiress of
Yotsuba Enterprises
, an extremely successful business conglomerate. She is gentle and quiet, and has a somewhat bubbly manner and is always calm. Due to her upbringing, she is a girl of many talents, from music to martial arts to cooking. However, she sometimes says or does things which deviate from popular sentiment, shocking her friends, or just show it by going and introducing things and places owned by
Yotsuba Industries
, and consequently, owned by her.

Despite her quiet nature, her anger is something to be wary of. Though rare, she can have powerful releases of her rage, especially if someone makes fun of or hurts her friends' feelings, and is very capable of beating up the ones at fault. Once calm and in control, she later regrets hurting them.

name: Yukishiro Honoka
season: Futari wa Pretty Cure Max Heart
personality:
Honoka is a gentle and understanding girl who always put others before herself. She is very smart, even being called the "The Queen of Knowledge
 (
知識の女王
,

Chishiki no joō
)
", "The Queen of Intelligence
 (
知性の女王
,

Chisei no joō
)
" or "The Queen of Wisdom
 (
叡智の女王
,

Eichi no joō
)
" by her classmates, and often uses this to help people. Due to this, she is very popular, having caught the attention of nearly every boy in school. She is not interested in most of them, but she has shown to care very much for a few boys, namely
Fujimura Shougo
, her childhood friend, and
Kiriya
, a new boy at school who she is helping understand people's feelings.

As she is serious about her passions, Honoka can be strict with others and can become forceful or scary if angered by other's laziness or lack of concern. However, she is shown to be this way out of care for said person and waning them to do their best. She can also be pushy in her attempts to help someone, and she has a surprisingly stubborn side. For the most part, she is usually easy-going and calm-tempered, not likely to be easily riled up in comparison to Nagisa.

name: Yumehara Nozomi
personality:
Nozomi is a caring person with a big heart and an optimistic outlook on life. While realizing she may not be talented or have any usable skills, she makes up for it by being very friendly and kind towards others, even to her enemies. A bit of a late thinker, she sometimes gets distracted, especially when food is involved. She is also childish, loud, clumsy, and does not seem to make decisions rationally.

As Cure Dream, she is noticeably more serious. She also gains more strength and never hesitates to help others.

name: Yuni
personality:
As Mao, she is very friendly and acts cutesy towards others. As it turns out, it was merely an act she puts on to conceal her true identity as a thief.

As Blue Cat, she is shown to be cunning, by using the bright fireworks to make her break with the Princess Star Color Pen and Madoka's plan to use the star donuts as bargaining chips to win the pen at the Auction. According to Lala, she always gets what she seeks.

As Yuni, she is a lone wolf and generally holds a strong responsibility for herself. This is mainly rooted from the guilt she has of being unable to save Planet Rainbow, causing her to reject her friends' kind offers and assistance in the beginning, and blaming herself when she fails to accomplish her goals. However, she gradually warms up to them as the series goes on. Despite all this, Yuni is still kindhearted, and she would help and rescue the needy, and has since grown to give up her prejudice, particularly toward Aiwarn.

Despite being a major heroine, Yuni is overall a morally gray character; on one hand, she is learning to be heroic enough to save the universe, but on the other hand, she still thieves the plundered treasures of Planet Rainbow.

name: Yuunagi Tsubasa
personality: Tsubasa is a hard worker who cares about Ellee-chan. Tsubasa dreams of being able to fly, so he studies very hard to make it happen. He struggles to express his emotions and doesn't like being pushed around. However, Tsubasa trusts those who have faith in him.
